text:
Lightly the breeze laughs in her sunlit castle;  
The bee goes murmuring in a dull ear;  
Sweet birds are piping in unwitting rhythm, --  
Ah, what wisdom vanished here!

source_text:
Light laughs the breeze in her castle of sunshine;
Babbles the bee in a stolid ear;
Pipe the sweet birds in ignorant cadence, --
Ah, what sagacity perished here!

text:
Let me drink deep of that sweet-sounding spirit,
More, oh more—I am still parched for it;
It loosens the serpent care has coiled around
My heart to keep its breath from it;
That unbinding melody, through every vein,
Flows into heart and mind again.

source_text:
Let me drink of the spirit of that sweet sound,
More, oh more,—I am thirsting yet;
It loosens the serpent which care has bound
Upon my heart to stifle it;
The dissolving strain, through every vein,
Passes into my heart and brain.
